---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import ArticleStats from '../../../components/ArticleStats.astro';

import apriCaughtShowers from '../../../assets/writings/apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co/01-apri-caught-showers.jpg';
import spicyGingerMule from '../../../assets/writings/apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co/02-spicy-ginger-mule.jpg';
import cocktailRecipe from '../../../assets/writings/apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co/03-cocktail-recipe.jpg';
import giveaway from '../../../assets/writings/apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co/04-giveaway.jpg';
import finalDrink from '../../../assets/writings/apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co/05-final-drink.jpg';
---

<Base title="Apri-caught Showers from American Cococktail Co. — Vivian Cromwell" activeNav="writings">
  <div class="painting-back">
    <a href="/writings" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Writings</a>
  </div>

  <article class="article" data-pagefind-body>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1 class="article-title">Apri-caught Showers from American Cococktail Co.</h1>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <time datetime="2020-04-11">April 11, 2020</time>
        <span class="article-meta-sep">&middot;</span>
        <span class="article-reading-time">3 min read</span>
        <span class="article-meta-sep">&middot;</span>
        <a href="/writings?category=wine-spirits" class="article-category">Wine & Spirits</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="article-body">
      <p>Last month, I had the pleasure to work with American Cocktail Co to design the upcoming April box: The Spicy Ginger Mule. This is a bourbon-based mule with the notes of apricot, just in time for the spring weather to enjoy at home.</p>

      <figure class="article-image">
        <Image src={apriCaughtShowers} alt="Apri-caught Showers cocktail" widths={[600, 900, 1200]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 700px" loading="eager" />
      </figure>

      <p>A little bit about American Cocktail Co: In 2012, while working at The Jefferson Hotel in Washington DC, Christoper Wirth teamed up with his friend Massimiliano Matte, a renowned mixologist to found American Cocktail Co. Their goal is to turn the evolution into a revolution by creating incredible unique juice blends and making them widely available.</p>

      <p>The particular blend I used in my drink is the Spicy Ginger Mule mix. It is firey with fresh, cold-pressed ginger, not to mention it is gluten-free, vegan and all-natural ingredients.</p>

      <figure class="article-image">
        <Image src={spicyGingerMule} alt="Spicy Ginger Mule mix from American Cocktail Co" widths={[600, 900, 1200]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 700px" loading="eager" />
        <figcaption>img source: americancocktailco.com</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <p>The specific drink I designed is called Apri-caught Showers, a play on the fruit apricot used in the drink.</p>

      <figure class="article-image">
        <Image src={cocktailRecipe} alt="Apri-caught Showers cocktail preparation" widths={[600, 900, 1200]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 700px" loading="lazy" />
      </figure>

      <h2>Apri-caught Showers</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>1 oz Spicy Ginger Mule</li>
        <li>1.5 oz Bulleit Bourbon</li>
        <li>Q club soda</li>
        <li>Dehydrated Apricot</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Soak dried apricot in the bourbon overnight. Pour infused bourbon and Spicy Ginger Mule mix into a rocks glass and top with soda.</p>

      <p>The kit has everything you need to make four drinks except mint. You can use TIPSYMUSE10 to get 10% off upon checkout.</p>

      <p>I also have a GIVEAWAY at the moment. Check it out at <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/B-2HGWxF4XD/">Instagram</a>. You and your friend will get not just one box, but two to share virtually!</p>

      <figure class="article-image">
        <Image src={giveaway} alt="American Cocktail Co giveaway" widths={[600, 900, 1200]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 700px" loading="lazy" />
      </figure>

      <p>American Cocktail Co. also did a nice interview with me about where I get my cocktail inspiration and my background. If you are interested, give it a read.</p>

      <figure class="article-image">
        <Image src={finalDrink} alt="Apri-caught Showers final presentation" widths={[600, 900, 1200]} sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 700px" loading="lazy" />
      </figure>

      <p>Stay well and healthy during this difficult time. Enjoy some nice homemade cocktails, made possible by American Cocktail Co.</p>

      <p><em>This post is sponsored by American Cocktail Co.</em></p>
    </div>

    <ArticleStats slug="apri-caught-showers-from-american-cococktail-co" tags={["bourbon", "cocktails"]} />
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
